<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-08T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-08T22:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2600</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-09T12:00:00+09:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1917, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My telegram June 8, 10 p.m. The Press today shows general irritation at
                            the communication made by Reinsch to China which is viewed as
                            interference in the latter’s internal politics and a further indication
                            of objectionable activity of the Legation at Peking. The Foreign Office
                            assumed that our proposal contemplated joint as well as identic
                            representation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>